t if not sure.";i:32;s:24:"And now the stabilities.";i:33;s:76:"For each chair conformer add the energy of all the groups on axial position.";i:34;s:155:"This tutorial along with a tutorial video show you my step by step method for drawing a hexagon cyclohexane chair conformation and simple ring flip method.";i:35;s:132:"The focus of this tutorial is speed and simplicity to ensure maximum points and minimum wasted timeeffort on your next quiz or exam.";i:36;s:154:"To draw the chair conformation of D-glucose you need to know the orientations of the axial and equatorial bonds on carbon atoms of the chair conformation.";i:37;s:79:"Below you can see how to determine what goes up and what goes down on the ring.";i:38;s:67:"A chair conformation of D- glucose with equatorial and axial bonds.";i:39;s:80:"Just three pairs of parallel lines and youve drawn a perfect chair conformation.";i:40;s:73:"But to draw them naturally to get them flowing off your pen and onto the.";i:41;s:37:"Require breaking and making of bonds.";i:42;s:93:"Chiral centers - absolute stereochemistry Configurational isomers cis and trans olefins Note.";i:43;s:110:"No acetylenes C C H C 2H 5 H 3C H C C C 2H 5 H H 3C H trans E entgegen opposite cis Z zusammen together Rules.";i:44;s:47:"Largest atomic number first 8O 7N 6C I Br Cl F.";i:45;s:95:"Drawing the cyclohexane chair conformations adds unnecessary stress to most chemistry students.";i:46;s:154:"Follow the steps below to easily draw the chair conformation and ring flips like a pro so you can focus your mental energy on solving the reaction itself.";i:47;s:66:"Consider The Pocket Chemist to help get your homework done faster.";i:48;s:128:"For most classes all you will need to know how to do is use equatorial preference to predict the most stable chair conformation.";i:49;s:198:"However sometimes you will be required to use energetics to calculate the exact percentages of each chair in solutionThis is a multistep process so here Im going to walk you through it from scratch.";i:50;s:39:"Just like you would name a cyclohexane.";i:51;s:56:"Convert the chair conformation to the ring conformation.";i:52;s:111:"It should make things easier If something is up that means that it would be on a bold wedge on the hexans ring.";i:53;s:31:"If something is down it should.";i:54;s:115:"In a chair conformation the bond angles for each carbon are about 109 degrees so the tetrahedrals are pretty close.";i:55;s:124:"Actually these bonds are a bit wobbly too enough for the carbons to wobble between boat and chair conformations on occasion.";}}